Feature: Character Creation and Classes # features/character_creation.feature:1

  Scenario: Creating a new character                                              # features/character_creation.feature:3
    Given a new player wants to start the game                                    # features/steps/character_steps.py:10
    When they access the character creation screen                                # features/steps/character_steps.py:24
    Then they should be presented with 23 unique character classes to choose from # features/steps/character_steps.py:34
    And each class should have distinct starting stats                            # features/steps/character_steps.py:39
    And each class should have unique gameplay mechanics                          # features/steps/character_steps.py:57
    And each class should have access to at least 10 unique abilities             # features/steps/character_steps.py:70
    And the character creation should include name selection                      # features/steps/character_steps.py:86
    And the character creation should include visual customization (text-based)   # features/steps/character_steps.py:90

  Scenario: Character class balance                                                     # features/character_creation.feature:13
    Given the game has 23 character classes                                             # features/steps/character_steps.py:94
    When comparing class statistics                                                     # features/steps/character_steps.py:109
    Then no class should be more than 15% more powerful than any other class            # features/steps/character_steps.py:114
    And each class should have clear strengths and weaknesses                           # features/steps/character_steps.py:119
    And each class should have at least one unique mechanic not shared by other classes # features/steps/character_steps.py:137

